ormal source adapters and one adapter that raises an unavailable error; assert run completes, output includes a `data unavailable` marker only for the failed section, and process does not abort.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The behavior is explicitly about summary content accuracy, which depends on model judgment/generation quality. A deterministic stub would always pass and hide real hallucination/omission errors. Rejection gate: Integration is disqualified by behavior text \"accurately represents\" because that requires evaluating real generated output content, not just call plumbing. Workflow is disqualified because this describes one summary-generation decision, not multiple agentic stages in sequence.","test_description":"Execute summary generation against representative real input datasets using the actual model/service and assert key facts (critical metrics, counts, deployment status) are preserved with acceptable accuracy thresholds across repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary includes real external delivery and inbox receipt, which requires real HTTP/API and email infrastructure behavior. In-process mocks can hide transport/auth/provider quirks and inbox routing issues. Rejection gate: Integration is disqualified by behavior text \"reaches ... inbox correctly,\" which cannot be proven with only local module wiring. Agentic is not required because correctness target here is end-to-end delivery, not model output quality.","test_description":"Run the scheduled/report pipeline end-to-end in a test environment against real source endpoints (or staging equivalents) and real email delivery path to a test mailbox; assert message arrival, recipients, subject/body presence, and attached/embedded report integrity.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.16,"System":0.74,"Agentic":0.07,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Core failure is orchestration/state handoff across modules: delivery failure handling -> filesystem persistence -> next-run retry. Integration-brake check: (a) real external outage is not strictly necessary; an in-process email adapter error plus real local temp filesystem can reproduce it, so System is not strictly minimum. (b) no dependence on AI/ML output, so Agentic is disqualified. (c) no multi-agentic chain, so Workflow is disqualified. Rejection gate: System considered due \"service is unreachable,\" but behavior text focuses on fallback+retry logic, which can be validated without real provider/network.","test_description":"Use real retry/persistence modules with an email adapter configured to fail first run and succeed second run; run scheduler trigger twice (or invoke run entrypoint twice with persisted state), assert report file is written after first failure and second run consumes persisted report and sends successfully.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.07,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.35,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
